<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-34-0877 </DOCNO><TEXT>The status of the measurement, monitoring, and modelling of acid-formingemissions in Alberta is reviewed in the context of managing an integratedenvironmental system. The need for sensitive sampling methods for usein studies such as the Acid Deposition Research Program is apparent andone such system, the Kananaskis Atmospheric Pollutant Sampler is describedand preliminary results presented. Future thrusts in the areas of measurement,monitoring, modelling, and management of importance to Alberta are outlined.37 refs., 3 figs., 4 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>